#MEM id=felix source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Finance/felix/FINANCE-PRINCIPLES.md
M|felix|> Load this file before preparing any financial report, model, or investor update.
M|felix|Felix applies different frameworks to each vtr because they have different business models:
M|felix|| Metric | Formula | Benchmark |
M|felix||--------|---------|-----------|
M|felix|| Gross Margin | (Revenue − COGS) / Revenue | Fashion e-commerce: 40–60% |
M|felix|| Net Margin | Net Income / Revenue | Target: 15–25% |
M|felix|| Inventory Turnover | COGS / Avg Inventory | Higher = better; target ≥ 4× |
M|felix|| CAC | mkt Spend / New Customers | Depends on channel mix |
M|felix|| ROAS | Revenue from Ads / Ad Spend | Target ≥ 3× |
M|felix|| Runway | Cash Reserves / Monthly Burn | Alert: < 6 months |
M|felix|Key P&L line items for Novizio:
M|felix|- Revenue (gross sales − returns)
M|felix|- COGS (prd, materials, fulfillment)
M|felix|- Gross Profit
M|felix|- mkt & Ads
M|felix|- Operations (tools, admin)
M|felix|- Net Profit/Loss
M|felix|| Metric | Formula | Benchmark |
M|felix||--------|---------|-----------|
M|felix|| MRR | Σ (monthly subscription revenue) | Track monthly growth % |
M|felix|| ARR | MRR × 12 | Investor-facing metric |
M|felix|| Churn Rate | Churned MRR / Prior MRR | Target: < 3% monthly |
M|felix|| Net Revenue Retention | (MRR + Expansion − Churn) / Prior MRR | Target: > 100% |
M|felix|| CAC | Sales & mkt Spend / New Customers | Payback period target: < 12 months |
M|felix|| LTV | ARPU / Churn Rate | Or: ARPU × Avg Customer Lifetime |
M|felix|| LTV:CAC | LTV / CAC | Healthy: ≥ 3:1 |
M|felix|| Burn Rate | Monthly Expenses − Monthly Revenue | Track net burn |
M|felix|| Runway | Cash Reserves / Net Burn | Alert: < 6 months |
M|felix|Key SaaS P&L line items for Hourbour:
M|felix|- MRR (new + expansion − churn)
M|felix|- Infrastructure / hosting
M|felix|- dev costs
M|felix|- Customer acquisition (ads, cnt)
M|felix|- Operations
M|felix|- Net Burn / Net Income
M|felix|Felix produces monthly P&L reports in this format:
M|felix|```markdown
M|felix|| Source | Amount | vs Prior Month | vs Target |
M|felix||--------|--------|---------------|----------|
M|felix|| [Source] | $X | +X% | +X% |
M|felix|| **Total Revenue** | **$X** | **+X%** | **+X%** |
M|felix|| Category | Amount | vs Prior Month | vs Budget |
M|felix||---------|--------|---------------|----------|
M|felix|| [Category] | $X | +X% | +X% |
M|felix|| **Total Expenses** | **$X** | **+X%** | **+X%** |
M|felix|| | Amount |
M|felix||-|--------|
M|felix|| Gross Profit | $X |
M|felix|| Gross Margin | X% |
M|felix|| Net Profit / (Loss) | $X |
M|felix|| Net Margin | X% |
M|felix|| Cash Runway | X months |
M|felix|1. [Most important trend — positive or negative]
M|felix|2. [Second observation]
M|felix|- [Any metric significantly off target — with proposed action]
M|felix|```
M|felix|```markdown
M|felix|| Metric | This Month | Prior Month | MoM Change | Target |
M|felix||--------|-----------|------------|-----------|--------|
M|felix|| MRR | $X | $X | +X% | $X |
M|felix|| New MRR | $X | — | — | — |
M|felix|| Expansion MRR | $X | — | — | — |
M|felix|| Churned MRR | ($X) | — | — | — |
M|felix|| Net MRR Growth | $X | — | — | — |
M|felix|| Total Users | X | X | +X% | — |
M|felix|| Paying Users | X | X | +X% | X |
M|felix|| Churn Rate | X% | X% | — | <3% |
M|felix|| LTV:CAC | X:1 | — | — | ≥3:1 |
M|felix|| Burn Rate | $X/mo | — | — | — |
M|felix|| Runway | X months | — | — | >6mo |
